contentrichtext.text: '''K6''' or '''K-6''' may refer to: ; Locations * [[K-6 (Kansas highway)]], a state highway in Kansas * [[K6 (mountain)]], a mountain in Pakistan * [[K6 pipe]], a geological formation in Northern Alberta, Canada ; Transportation * [[HMS K6]], a British submarine * [[USS K-6 (SS-37)]], a 1914 United States Navy K-class submarine * [[Schleicher Ka 6|Ka 6]], a glider manufactured by Alexander Schleicher GmbH & Co, Germany * K6, IATA code for [[Bravo Air Congo]] ; Other uses * [[K-6 (education)]], the grades which are traditionally grouped together in American elementary schools; formerly Kindergarten through sixth grade * [[K6 HMG]], a 12.7mm heavy machine gun of South Korea * [[K6 Telephone Kiosk]], a Red telephone boxes model in use the United Kingdom since 1935 * [[AMD K6]], a computer microprocessor * [[Violin Sonatas, KV 6-9 (Mozart)|Sonata in C for Keyboard and Violin]], sixth work by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart according to the KÃ¶chel catalogue * [[Grushin K-6]], a Soviet [[Air to air missile]] developed in the 1950s {{Letter-NumberCombDisambig}}
